When WASHINGTON made his last tour, through the Nothern States, and had reached the vicinity of Portsmouth, the question was asked, what title shall we give him? The venerable DOCTOR HAVEN replied, in the true sublime;
Fame spread her wings, and with her trumpet blew;
Great WASHINGTON is near! What praise HIS due!
What TITLE shall he have? She paus'd, and said,
NOT ONE, HIS NAME ALONE STRIKES EVERY TITLE DEAD.
GEORGE WASHINGTON, was born 11 February, 1732, at the Parish of Washington, in the county of Westmoreland, and state of Virginia. He was appointed Commander in Chief of the American Armies, in 1775. He resigned his Commission, in 17 •• . He was chosen President of the United States, in 1789. He resigned the Presidency, in 1796. He died at Mount Vernon, between the hours of 10 and 11, Saturday evening, the 14 December, 1799.
